ESMFold Structure Visualization

Interactive 3D visualization of predicted protein structures from ESMFold.

Input: 736 amino acid sequence
Output: structure_1.pdb with 3D atomic coordinates

In[2]:
import py3Dmol
from pathlib import Path

# Path to the predicted structure and input sequence
pdb_file = Path("experiments/exp1/structures/structure_1.pdb")
input_file = Path("experiments/exp1/raw.txt")

# Read the input sequence
with open(input_file, 'r') as f:
    raw_input = f.read().strip()

# Parse sequence (format: "index sequence")
parts = raw_input.split(None, 1)
sequence = parts[1] if len(parts) > 1 else parts[0]

# Read the PDB file
with open(pdb_file, 'r') as f:
    pdb_content = f.read()

print("=" * 80)
print(" INPUT SEQUENCE")
print("=" * 80)
print(f"Length: {len(sequence)} amino acids\n")

# Print sequence in blocks of 60 characters (standard format)
for i in range(0, len(sequence), 60):
    line_num = f"{i+1:>4}"
    seq_block = sequence[i:i+60]
    # Add spacing every 10 characters for readability
    formatted = ' '.join([seq_block[j:j+10] for j in range(0, len(seq_block), 10)])
    print(f"{line_num}  {formatted}")

print()
print("=" * 80)
print(" OUTPUT STRUCTURE")
print("=" * 80)
print(f"PDB file: {pdb_file}")
print(f"File size: {len(pdb_content):,} characters")

Cartoon View (Rainbow by Sequence Position)

In[3]:
# Create 3D viewer - Cartoon style (shows alpha helices and beta sheets)
viewer = py3Dmol.view(width=800, height=600)
viewer.addModel(pdb_content, 'pdb')

# Color by sequence position (N-terminus=blue to C-terminus=red)
viewer.setStyle({'cartoon': {'color': 'spectrum'}})
viewer.setBackgroundColor('white')
viewer.zoomTo()
viewer.show()

3Dmol.js failed to load for some reason. Please check your browser console for error messages.

Colored by pLDDT Confidence Score

ESMFold provides per-residue confidence scores (pLDDT) stored in the B-factor column:

  • Blue (> 0.9): Very high confidence
  • Cyan (0.7-0.9): Confident
  • Yellow (0.5-0.7): Low confidence
  • Orange/Red (< 0.5): Very low confidence
In[4]:
# Create viewer colored by confidence (B-factor/pLDDT)
viewer2 = py3Dmol.view(width=800, height=600)
viewer2.addModel(pdb_content, 'pdb')

# Color by B-factor (pLDDT confidence score)
viewer2.setStyle({'cartoon': {'colorscheme': {'prop': 'b', 'gradient': 'roygb', 'min': 0, 'max': 1}}})
viewer2.setBackgroundColor('white')
viewer2.zoomTo()
viewer2.show()

Structure Statistics & pLDDT Analysis

In[5]:
from Bio.PDB import PDBParser
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Parse PDB file
parser = PDBParser(QUIET=True)
structure = parser.get_structure('protein', pdb_file)

# Get statistics
model = structure[0]
chain = model['A']

residues = list(chain.get_residues())
atoms = list(chain.get_atoms())

# Extract B-factors (pLDDT scores)
ca_atoms = [atom for atom in atoms if atom.get_name() == 'CA']
plddt_scores = [atom.get_bfactor() for atom in ca_atoms]

print(" Structure Statistics:")
print(f"   Number of residues: {len(residues)}")
print(f"   Number of atoms: {len(atoms)}")
print()
print(" pLDDT Confidence Scores:")
print(f"   Mean pLDDT: {np.mean(plddt_scores):.3f}")
print(f"   Min pLDDT:  {np.min(plddt_scores):.3f}")
print(f"   Max pLDDT:  {np.max(plddt_scores):.3f}")
print()
print(" Confidence Distribution:")
high_conf = sum(1 for s in plddt_scores if s > 0.9)
med_conf = sum(1 for s in plddt_scores if 0.7 <= s <= 0.9)
low_conf = sum(1 for s in plddt_scores if s < 0.7)
print(f"   High (> 0.9):     {high_conf} residues ({100*high_conf/len(plddt_scores):.1f}%)")
print(f"   Medium (0.7-0.9): {med_conf} residues ({100*med_conf/len(plddt_scores):.1f}%)")
print(f"   Low (< 0.7):      {low_conf} residues ({100*low_conf/len(plddt_scores):.1f}%)")

In[6]:
# Plot pLDDT scores along the sequence
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(14, 4))

residue_numbers = range(1, len(plddt_scores) + 1)
colors = ['#1E88E5' if s > 0.9 else '#00ACC1' if s > 0.7 else '#FDD835' if s > 0.5 else '#FF7043' for s in plddt_scores]

ax.bar(residue_numbers, plddt_scores, color=colors, width=1.0)
ax.axhline(y=0.9, color='blue', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5, label='Very high (0.9)')
ax.axhline(y=0.7, color='cyan', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5, label='Confident (0.7)')
ax.axhline(y=0.5, color='yellow', linestyle='--', alpha=0.5, label='Low (0.5)')

ax.set_xlabel('Residue Number', fontsize=12)
ax.set_ylabel('pLDDT Score', fontsize=12)
ax.set_title('ESMFold Confidence Score per Residue', fontsize=14)
ax.set_ylim(0, 1)
ax.legend(loc='lower right')
ax.grid(True, alpha=0.3)

plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
